sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM analysis_logs 
WHERE user_id = 1;

SELECT AVG(score_id) AS avg_score_id
FROM sentiment_scores
WHERE sentiment_algorithm = 'VADER';

external_knowledge:
- 'VADER sentiment score below 0.5' implies a negative sentiment; 
- 'Sentiment change is declined' means the sentiment has become more negative over time; 
- 'Retweeted more than 20 times' indicates a certain level of engagement or popularity; 
- 'TextBlob sentiment score' provides an alternative measure of sentiment for comparison with VADER.

- Having a 'pulse on the hearts of people' refers to the brands being popular and well-liked; 
- 'most favored in terms of likes' means having the highest total number of likes; 
- 'overall sentiment resonates with the emotions of the majority of their audience' means the sentiment label of the brand matches the sentiment of most of its tweets.
